						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the ruined temple of Śiva.</p>						

						<p>1576 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1498, Dhātu, Vaiśākha, su. 10 corresponding to 1576 A.D. April 8, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>It records the consecration of the god Gōpala-kṛishṇamma at Kūchanapalli and the gift of land 3 <hi rend="italic">kuchaḍlu (kunchālu ?)</hi> by Dīpānāyumḍu of Poṭapalli for maintaining the <hi rend="italic">amṛitapaḍi</hi> service to the god. The second side contains three imprecatory verse <hi rend="italic">‘svadattam’.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
